[h1]DST Mod Publisher[/h1]

[b]A modern Workshop uploader for Don't Starve modders — just keep Steam running. A drop-in replacement for the official ModUploader.[/b]
[img]https://images.steamusercontent.com/ugc/13762441291674141972/C09A22296D9E12543A2697D19567A690CA4239FC/?imw=637&imh=358&ima=fit&impolicy=Letterbox&imcolor=%23000000&letterbox=true[/img]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Why this exists[/h2]
If you've used the official uploader, you know the pain:
[list]
[*]One failed upload and your carefully written description is [b]wiped clean[/b]
[*]Want to fix a typo in the description? Re-upload the whole mod
[*]The description box is a bare textarea — BBCode written blind, one language only
[*]It uploads your entire folder: .git, PSD sources, backup archives, everything
[*]No change notes — subscribers never know what you changed
[*]Version number is edited by hand in modinfo.lua; forget it and the update fails silently
[*]Errors are just a number. What's EResult 25? Go figure
[/list]

[h2]What this tool does about it[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Zero setup[/b] — Steam running + an account that owns Don't Starve. Unzip, double-click, done. No login, no password, no dependencies (same Steamworks mechanism as the official tool)
[*][b]Draft autosave[/b] — everything you type is saved as you go; a failed upload keeps your work intact, fix and retry
[*][b]Multi-language descriptions[/b] — edit title and description per language (EN / Simplified & Traditional Chinese / JP / KR / RU), just like the Steam backend; existing workshop text is pulled in as your baseline
[*][b]BBCode editor[/b] — every Steam tag (headers, lists, tables, quotes, code, spoilers, video) with live preview
[*][b]Selective updates[/b] — tick what to update this time: content files / title & description / preview image / tags / visibility. A description-only fix takes seconds, no file re-upload
[*][b]Change notes[/b] — write a changenote per update; it lands in Steam's official Change Notes tab
[*][b]Clean uploads[/b] — ignores .git / exported / source files / archives / exe by default; the file list is visible before upload, [b]click any file to toggle upload/ignore[/b], your choice is remembered; .modignore rules supported too
[*][b]Version automation[/b] — one-click bump written back to modinfo.lua, the workshop version: tag maintained automatically, and updates are blocked unless the version is higher than what's live
[*][b]mod.manifest[/b] — generated automatically on publish (the game's asset index, same as the official uploader), so mod assets load faster
[*][b]Workshop overview[/b] — covers, subscriptions, favorites, comment counts and rating for all your items on one screen, multi-select tag filtering, one click to the comments page
[*][b]Target and content decoupled[/b] — pick the workshop item (or "new item") and the content folder independently; visibility, tags and descriptions all default to what's currently live, so updating an old item from a new machine or folder just works
[*][b]The tool updates itself[/b] — it tells you when a new version is out and upgrades with one click; if you're subscribed to this page, Steam even delivers the package so there's nothing to download
[*][b]Errors in plain language[/b] — EResult codes are translated with suggested fixes
[*][b]Modern UI[/b] — Material You design, dark mode, 14 theme colors
[/list]

[h2]Three steps to start[/h2]
[olist]
[*]Download and unzip the release; make sure the Steam client is logged in
[*]Double-click dst_mod_publisher.exe and pick your mods directory in Settings
[*]Hit "Update" on the Workshop page, or pick a folder on the Publish page → fill in version and notes → publish
[/olist]

[h2]How to get it[/h2]
[olist]
[*][b]Subscribe to this page[/b] and let Steam finish downloading
[*]Open [b]steamapps/workshop/content/322330/THIS-ITEM-ID/[/b] (the numeric ID is in your browser's address bar)
[*]Unzip [b]DSTModPublisher-windows.zip[/b] inside and double-click dst_mod_publisher.exe — zero dependencies, just have Steam running
[/olist]
You only do this once: when a new version ships, the tool will offer to update itself.

[h2]Open source[/h2]
[list]
[*]GPL-3.0: [url=https://github.com/HuanYue-NoPrediction/ConstantPublisher]GitHub repository[/url] (source and Releases; the copy on this page is kept in sync)
[*]Experimental macOS build available in GitHub Releases (unsigned, in testing)
[*]Two engines: Steamworks by default on desktop, plus a steamcmd engine for CI / headless automation
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[i]This is a community tool, not affiliated with Klei Entertainment or Valve. Don't Starve is a trademark of Klei Entertainment; Steam is a trademark of Valve. While uploading, Steam may show you as "playing Don't Starve Together" — that's normal for Steamworks integrations.[/i]
